The paper discusses the privacy and security implications of BitTorrent Sync, which is a peer-to-peer file synchronization service. This topic falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR) and distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC). The paper also discusses the potential forensic implications of BitTorrent Sync, which could fall under the categories of cybercrime (cs.CY), formal languages and automata theory (cs.FL), and software engineering (cs.SE).
